quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  100,10,"and when whatever lies within the hearts is obtained—"
  101,1,"The Shocking Event!"
  101,2,"What is the Shocking Event?"
  101,3,"And what can make yousg realize what the Shocking Event is?"
  101,4,"A day when mankind become like scattered moths,"
  101,5,"and the mountains become like tufted wool."
  101,6,"So, as for the one whose scales were heavy1—"
  101,7,"he is in a pleasant life."
  101,8,"But as for the one whose scales were lightb —"
  101,9,"his home1is an Abyss."
  101,10,"And what can make yousg realize what it is?"
  102,1,"Vying for more distracted youpl"
  102,2,"until you visited the graves."
  102,3,"But no! Youpl will come to know."
  102,4,"Once again: But no! Youpl will come to know."
  102,5,"But no! If only youpl knew with the knowledge of certitude:"
  102,6,"you will certainly see1 purgatory."
  102,7,"Then youpl will certainly see it with the eye of certitude."
  102,8,"Then, on that day, youpl will certainly be asked about(worldly) bliss."